Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
HR Leave & Attendance Management System (3 Roles)
1. Purpose

The purpose of this system is to provide a simple internal web application for an organization to:

manage employee profiles,

handle leave requests with approval workflow,

maintain leave balances,

record manual attendance,

maintain a holiday calendar, and

generate monthly summaries for HR review and payroll support.

This system is designed for small-to-medium teams where attendance is maintained manually and leave approvals follow a reporting-manager workflow.

2. Scope
2.1 In-Scope Features (MVP)

The system will include the following modules:

Employee Management

Add, update, deactivate employees

Assign reporting manager

Maintain department/designation details

Leave Management

Leave request application (employee)

Leave approval/rejection (manager)

Leave request tracking and history

Leave cancellation (employee for pending leaves)

Leave Balance Management

View leave balance (employee)

Allocate/adjust leave balances (admin)

Auto update balance on approval/cancellation

Attendance Management (Manual)

Employee marks their attendance (Present/WFH/Half-day)

Admin can mark/correct attendance for any employee

Attendance monthly view for employee and admin

Holiday Calendar

Maintain holiday list (admin)

View holidays (all roles)

Reports

Monthly leave summary (admin; manager for team; employee for self)

Monthly attendance summary (admin; manager for team; employee for self)

Export as CSV (optional but recommended)

2.2 Out of Scope (for this project)

These are intentionally excluded to keep the project small:

Payroll processing and salary calculation

Biometric/device attendance integration

Geo-location attendance and selfie verification

Advanced leave policies (carry-forward, encashment, accrual per month)

Multi-branch/region holiday variations (can be added later)

Shift scheduling and overtime calculations

3. Users and User Characteristics
3.1 User Roles

The system will support three roles:

A) Employee

Description: Any staff member who applies leaves and marks attendance.

Primary goals

Apply leave quickly and track approval status

See leave balance anytime

Mark daily attendance manually

View monthly attendance and holidays

Typical usage

Uses system daily (attendance) and occasionally (leave)

B) Manager

Description: A user who manages a team and approves/rejects leave requests from their direct reportees.

Primary goals

Review and approve/reject leave requests

View upcoming leaves to plan team availability

View team leave summaries (monthly)

Typical usage

Uses system when leave requests come in; checks team view occasionally

C) Admin (HR/Admin)

Description: HR or admin staff responsible for setting up employees, leave balances, holidays and reports.

Primary goals

Maintain employee list and reporting structure

Allocate and correct leave balances

Correct attendance issues

Generate reports for HR records and payroll support

Typical usage

Uses system daily/weekly for operations and monthly for reports

4. System Context (High-Level)
4.1 System Overview

This is a web-based management system with login-based access control. Users perform actions based on their role:

Employees apply leave and mark attendance

Managers approve/reject leave

Admin manages employees, policies (basic), attendance corrections, holidays, reports

5. Assumptions and Dependencies
Assumptions

Organization has a defined reporting manager for each employee (except admin)

Attendance is manual (no external device)

Leave types are predefined (CL/SL/EL/LWP) for MVP

Dependencies

Email/Password login system exists

File upload storage (only if leave attachment is included)

6. Functional Requirements (Role-wise)
6.1 Employee Requirements
FR-E1 Login & Access

Employee shall be able to login using credentials provided by Admin.

Employee shall only access their own leave and attendance data.

FR-E2 Apply Leave

Employee shall submit a leave request with:

leave type, start date, end date, reason, optional attachment

System shall prevent overlapping leave requests.

System shall validate leave balance (for paid leave types).

FR-E3 Track Leave Requests

Employee shall view list of their leave requests with status:

Pending / Approved / Rejected / Cancelled

Employee shall view manager comments on decision.

FR-E4 Cancel Leave

Employee shall be able to cancel a Pending leave request.

System shall update status to Cancelled.

FR-E5 View Leave Balance

Employee shall view available leave balance by leave type.

FR-E6 Mark Attendance (Manual)

Employee shall be able to mark attendance for the current day as:

Present / Work From Home / Half-day

System shall restrict multiple entries for same day.

FR-E7 View Attendance & Holidays

Employee shall view monthly attendance history.

Employee shall view holiday calendar.

6.2 Manager Requirements
FR-M1 View Team Members

Manager shall view a list of employees reporting to them.

FR-M2 Approve/Reject Leave

Manager shall view pending leave requests of team members.

Manager shall approve or reject with optional comments.

System shall notify employee via in-app status update.

FR-M3 Team Leave Visibility

Manager shall view approved leave schedule for team (list/calendar view).

FR-M4 Team Reports

Manager shall view monthly leave summary for their team.

6.3 Admin Requirements
FR-A1 Employee CRUD

Admin shall create, update, deactivate employees.

Admin shall assign a manager to an employee.

FR-A2 Leave Type Setup (MVP: fixed types)

Admin shall maintain leave types (optional if hardcoded).

FR-A3 Allocate Leave Balances

Admin shall allocate yearly leave balances for each employee.

Admin shall adjust balances if required (corrections).

FR-A4 Attendance Correction

Admin shall mark attendance for any employee for any day.

Admin shall edit/correct existing attendance entries with reason.

FR-A5 Holiday Management

Admin shall create, update, delete holidays.

FR-A6 Reports

Admin shall generate monthly:

leave summary reports

attendance summary reports

Admin shall filter reports by department/employee.

Admin shall export reports as CSV (optional).

7. Non-Functional Requirements (NFR)
NFR-1 Security & Access Control

Role-based access control must be enforced.

Employees must not access other employees’ records.

NFR-2 Usability

Simple UI with minimal steps:

Apply leave in ≤ 1 minute

Approve leave in ≤ 30 seconds

NFR-3 Performance

Normal operations should respond within 2 seconds for typical datasets (up to 500 employees).

NFR-4 Auditability (Recommended)

System should log key actions:

leave approval/rejection, attendance correction, balance edits

NFR-5 Data Integrity

No duplicate attendance entry for same employee/day.

No overlapping approved leaves for same employee.

8. Key Workflows
WF-1 Leave Application & Approval

Employee submits leave request → Status = Pending

Manager reviews → Approves or Rejects

If approved → leave balance reduced

Employee views status & comment

WF-2 Attendance Marking

Employee marks today’s attendance

Admin can later correct if wrong

Monthly attendance view updated

WF-3 Monthly Reporting

Admin selects month/year

System generates leave and attendance summaries

Admin exports file if needed

9. Constraints (for Small Project)

Manual attendance only

Simple leave balances (yearly allocation)

No advanced payroll/biometric integrations